						<div class="postbody">Oh, I didn't mean it was good for your demo. You certainly have made the right choices. I don't think there is a better way to handle that sort of rendering than using a lot of tables. When I was planning a raycaster for the NES (can't say if I'll ever make it) it also used a great deal of pre-calculated values.
<br />
<br />I meant that, as a general line-drawing algorithm, Bresenham was better than anything that included divisions, for example.</div>

